-- MOVES-BNP Paribas asset management division adds 4 executives
-- 
-- Mon Jul 14, 2014 10:05AM EDT
-- None



July 14 (Reuters) - BNP Paribas Securities Services, the asset management division of BNP Paribas <BNPP.PA>, said it added four executives to its team of UK asset managers.

Ken Back joined as head of asset managers and alternatives sales for the UK. He joins from Broadridge Financial Solutions. Anne Leyton was appointed head of the fund manager liaison team. She joins from Citigroup Inc <C.N>, where she was a client executive director working with large asset management clients. Roman Seydoux joined as global relationship manager for asset managers. Earlier, he worked with Bank of New York Mellon <BK.N>, where he was in charge of relationships with alternative investment managers.